726463f-b.text:
Cypress Hills Street (formerly Fresh Pond Road), west side, between 60th Lane and Myrtle Ave., showing in a set of four views the home and barn of Peter De Bevoise from 1860-1873. A George Pine occupied same about 1850. This house was demolished in 1923, the barn soon following; a one story garage occupying the site in 1929. Note View No. 3 shows the house to be a shambles while the barn remains. Seen in this latter view and across clearance are buildings on the west side of 64th Street between the
aforementioned streets.
1922.
Views 1,2 & 4.
View 3: March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726601f-a.text:
Flushing Ave. (viewed northward; trolley poles thereon), between 58th (Rust Street) (left) and 59th Street (right foreground), showing a rear view of homes belonging to the Cord Meyer Estate in 1891. These
homes face on Grand Ave.
January 1924.
Eucene L. Armbruster Collection.
